! Zen Mode for CodeMirror 6

Distraction-free writing environment for focused editing.

!! Features

* ''Fullscreen overlay'' — editor fills the viewport, hides TiddlyWiki chrome
* ''Centered content'' — comfortable max-width for readability
* ''Focus modes'' — dim surrounding text (line, sentence, or paragraph)
* ''Typewriter mode'' — keep cursor vertically centered
* ''Live statistics'' — word count, character count, reading time
* ''Theme integration'' — inherits your active CodeMirror theme
* ''Smooth transitions'' — fade in/out animations

!! Usage

Click the Zen Mode button in the editor toolbar, or use the keyboard shortcut:

* ''Ctrl+Shift+Z'' (default, configurable)

!! Exit Zen Mode

* Press ''Escape''
* Click the ''×'' close button
* Click outside the editor (if enabled in settings)

!! Focus Modes

|!Mode |!Description |
|None |No dimming |
|Line |Highlight current line only |
|Sentence |Highlight current sentence |
|Paragraph |Highlight current paragraph |

!! Settings

Configure Zen Mode in ''Control Panel → Settings → CodeMirror → Zen Mode''
